=== Etymology ===
Supposedly it was a name given to members of the Society of Friends in England when in his defense, the leader of the Society told the English judge he (that is the judge rather) would be the one to quake with fear before God on his Day of Judgment.

== [[noun]] ==
# a believer of the Quaker faith and a member of the Society of Friends, known for their pacifist views.

